final agreement. There still can be some changes,\" Feinstein said. \"But I don't think it's helpful for Israel to come out and oppose this one opportunity to change a major dynamic -- which is downhill, a downhill dynamic in this part of the world.\" Energy Secretary Ernest Moniz defended the deal in an appearance on CBS' \"Face the Nation\" on Sunday, saying it would extend from two months to one year the \"breakout\" time period -- the length of time it would take Iran to build a nuclear bomb. He said it also allows for the \"almost instantaneous recognition of any attempt to evade the deal.\" \"We have blocked all of these pathways to a bomb,\" he said. Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-South Carolina, said on"], "result": {"text": "28####Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has criticized the Iran nuclear deal, claiming that ratcheting up pressure is a better option than the deal or war. His comments have sparked a debate between Democrats and Republicans. Senator Lindsey Graham suggested that a new President could do better than Obama in negotiating a better deal."}}
